question: I’m bi and I’m rlly glad that’s it’s fucking canon that tony is too but like,,does hat mean mcu tony is bi? I hope so
answer:
i feel you im also bi and im so so so happy my favorite character of all time tony stark whom ive loved since i was 12 is now confirmed bi. clearly marvel comics is trying to explore his sexuality one step at the time and i dont doubt it’ll be a loooong time before we actually see him dating a guy but hey ill take whatever they give me honestly

on the other hand mcu tony is engaged and about to be a dad so like im pretty sure tony’s love life arc has reached it’s end. that being said, if we extrapolate a lot of characterization bits from the comics (like howard’s abuse, alcoholism, etc) we can also extrapolate this. im pretty sure we won’t see him say anything about being bisexual in the next two films and i doubt he’ll be in more, but hey if you ask rdj what he thinks he’ll definitely say mcu tony can also be bi.

title: Time Is Never Enough
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2NkZJEG

by SuperKatAmerica96

“What do you think you’ll be doing in five years, Bucky?” Steve asked his boyfriend. It was their Senior year of high school and they were trying to figure out their plans for the summer and the future. Bucky smiled and said, “I wouldn’t mind getting a degree in electrical engineering.” “You and your inventions.” Steve laughed. Bucky looked at his boyfriend and took hold of his hands. “But, that’s not the only thing I want to do.” Steve looked at him as Bucky pulled out a blue ring. “I want to marry you in five years.” Steve looked at the ring and smiled. “This is my sign as a promise that one day, I will propose to you because I will marry you.” Bucky said as he slid the ring onto Steve’s finger. “I love you, Bucky.” “I love you too, Steve.”
